        "avatar_template": "/letter_avatar_proxy/v4/letter/m/67e7ee/{size}.png",
        "created_at": "2021-01-11T03:19:53.000Z",
        "cooked": "<aside class=\"quote no-group\" data-post=\"3\" data-topic=\"167229\">\n<blockquote>\n<p>I drank a bottle last week. Delicious, and no \u201cmousiness\u201d.<br>\nI think that sometimes there can be a bit of reductiveness that blows off with air, but\u2026<br>\nDisclaimer, I import his wines.</p>\n</blockquote>\n</aside>\n<p>Good to know that it was showing well last week.</p>\n<p>How do you feel about drinking Marguet on the younger side vs with more bottle age (5-10+ years)?</p>\n<p>Drinking the Crayeres the other day, how patient were you with it? Did you decant?</p>",
